Program: Crossing Continents
Title: The Graves of Kashmir
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b018flpd
Last Broadcast Date: Boxing Day 2011
Jill McGivering, the BBC World Service South Asia editor, investigates the discovery of thousands of bodies in mass graves in Indian Kashmir. Human rights groups suspect they are just some of the victims of "disappearances" at the hands of the Indian military in this contested region. The authorities respond that the bodies are in fact those of militants who have infiltrated from Pakistan. Will an official investigation reveal the truth? Producer: Michael Gallagher. Show less